    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-hemolysis-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Normalized index of hemolysis comparison across 5 operating points",
      "description": "Predicted NIH values compared against in vitro hemolysis measurements at flow rates of 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min at 2500 RPM. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 satisfied at all operating points. The report acknowledges that donor-to-donor variability in red blood cell fragility introduces significant aleatory uncertainty in the experimental reference values; however, no hasUncertaintyQuantification node is linked to this ValidationResult, leaving the aleatory component formally uncharacterized."
    },
