    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements. Validation results demonstrate CFD model predicts hemolysis-relevant QoIs within pre-specified acceptance criteria across all five CPB operating points. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 satisfied, supporting the claim that the CFD model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Aleatory uncertainties associated with blood analog property variability and donor-to-donor RBC fragility variation are acknowledged in validation narratives; formal UQ characterization is recommended for future MRL 3 assessments.",
